        Serialize the desired nodetypes as a CND exported from the provided Session to the provided cndFile.
        Parameters:
        cndFile - a CND file to create or update with the desired JCR node type names.
        session - the JCR session
        desiredTypeNames - the list of nodetype names to export, usually determined by scanning a FileVault archive for jcr:primaryType and jcr:mixinTypes properties
        Throws:
        javax.jcr.RepositoryException - for missing nodetypes or any other repository exception
        IOException - for I/O errors
        org.apache.jackrabbit.commons.cnd.ParseException - if the initialCnd is not a valid CND file.

      • writeNodetypes

        public void writeNodetypes(@NotNull
                           @NotNull CndExporter.WriterOpener writerOpener,
                           @NotNull
                           @NotNull javax.jcr.Session session,
                           @NotNull
                           @NotNull List<String> desiredTypeNames,
                           @Nullable
                           @Nullable File initialCnd)
                    throws javax.jcr.RepositoryException,
                           IOException,
                           org.apache.jackrabbit.commons.cnd.ParseException
        Serialize the desired nodetypes as a CND to the provided stream writer.
        Parameters:
        writerOpener - an opener function that provides the desired output stream.
        session - the JCR session
        desiredTypeNames - the list of nodetype names to export, usually determined by scanning a FileVault archive for jcr:primaryType and jcr:mixinTypes properties
        initialCnd - an optional file providing a CND with an initial list of nodetype definitions. This will be read fully before the writerOpener is opened, so it is safe to read and write to the same file, in order to update its contents according to the rules of this exporter.
        Throws:
        javax.jcr.RepositoryException - for missing nodetypes or any other repository exception
        IOException - for I/O errors
        org.apache.jackrabbit.commons.cnd.ParseException - if the initialCnd is not a valid CND file.
